#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2065
#, no-wrap
msgid "Getting Started"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2069
msgid ""
"There are a few ways to obtain a working copy of the tree from Subversion.  "
"This section will explain them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2071
#, no-wrap
msgid "Direct Checkout"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2075
msgid ""
"The first is to check out directly from the main repository.  For the `src` "
"tree, use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2079
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2198
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn checkout svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/base/head /usr/src\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2082
msgid "For the `doc` tree, use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2086
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn checkout svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/doc/head /usr/doc\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2089
msgid "For the `ports` tree, use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2093
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn checkout svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/ports/head /usr/ports\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2099
msgid ""
"Though the remaining examples in this document are written with the workflow "
"of working with the `src` tree in mind, the underlying concepts are the same "
"for working with the `doc` and the `ports` tree.  Ports related Subversion "
"operations are listed in <<ports>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2103
msgid ""
"The above command will check out a `CURRENT` source tree as [.filename]#/usr/"
"src/#, which can be any target directory on the local filesystem.  Omitting "
"the final argument of that command causes the working copy, in this case, to "
"be named \"head\", but that can be renamed safely."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2106
msgid ""
"`svn+ssh` means the SVN protocol tunnelled over SSH.  The name of the server "
"is `repo.freebsd.org`, `base` is the path to the repository, and `head` is "
"the subdirectory within the repository."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2108
msgid ""
"If your FreeBSD login name is different from the login name used on the "
"local machine, either include it in the URL (for example `svn+ssh://"
"jarjar@repo.freebsd.org/base/head`), or add an entry to [.filename]#~/.ssh/"
"config# in the form:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2113
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Host repo.freebsd.org\n"
"\tUser jarjar\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2116
msgid ""
"This is the simplest method, but it is hard to tell just yet how much load "
"it will place on the repository."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2121
msgid ""
"The `svn diff` does not require access to the server as SVN stores a "
"reference copy of every file in the working copy.  This, however, means that "
"Subversion working copies are very large in size."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2124
#, no-wrap
msgid "`RELENG_*` Branches and General Layout"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2129
msgid ""
"In `ssh://gitrepo.freebsd.org/src.git`, _src_ refers to the source tree.  "
"Similarly, _ports_ refers to the ports tree, and so on.  These are separate "
"repositories with their own change number sequences, access controls and "
"commit mail."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2133
msgid ""
"For the src repository, `main` refers to the -CURRENT tree.  For example, [."
"filename]#head/bin/ls# is what would go into [.filename]#/usr/src/bin/ls# in "
"a release.  Some key branches are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2135
msgid "_main_ which corresponds to `HEAD`, also known as `-CURRENT`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2136
msgid "_stable/n_ which corresponds to `RELENG_n`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2137
msgid "_releng/n.n_ which corresponds to `RELENG_n_n`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2138
msgid "_release/n.n.n_ which corresponds to `RELENG_n_n_n_RELEASE`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2139
msgid "_vendor*_ is the vendor branch import work area."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2141
#, no-wrap
msgid "FreeBSD Documentation Project Branches and Layout"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2144
msgid ""
"In `ssh://gitrepo.freebsd.org/doc.git`, _doc_ refers to the repository of "
"the documentation tree."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2146
msgid ""
"In general, most FreeBSD Documentation Project work will be done within the "
"`main` branch of the documentation source tree."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2148
msgid ""
"FreeBSD documentation is written and/or translated to various languages, "
"each in a separate directory in the `main` branch."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2151
msgid ""
"Each translation set contains several subdirectories for the various parts "
"of the FreeBSD Documentation Project.  A few noteworthy directories are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2153
msgid ""
"_documentation/_ contains all the source code for the documentation part of "
"the tree."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2154
msgid ""
"_documentation/content/LANG/articles/_ contains the source code for articles "
"written by various FreeBSD contributors."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2155
msgid ""
"_documentation/content/LANG/books/_ contains the source code for the "
"different books, such as the FreeBSD Handbook."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2156
msgid "_website/_ contains the source code for the FreeBSD website."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2159
msgid ""
"LANG above is the two character language code.  All document source is "
"encoded using Unicode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2161
#, no-wrap
msgid "FreeBSD Ports Tree Branches and Layout"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2164
msgid ""
"In `svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/ports`, _ports_ refers to the repository root "
"of the ports tree."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2167
msgid ""
"In general, most FreeBSD port work will be done within the [.filename]#head/"
"# branch of the ports tree which is the actual ports tree used to install "
"software.  Some other key locations are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2169
msgid ""
"/branches/RELENG_n_n_n which corresponds to `RELENG_n_n_n` is used to merge "
"back security updates in preparation for a release."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2170
msgid ""
"/tags/RELEASE_n_n_n which corresponds to `RELEASE_n_n_n` represents a "
"release tag of the ports tree."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2171
msgid ""
"/tags/RELEASE_n_EOL represents the end of life tag of a specific FreeBSD "
"branch."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2173
#, no-wrap
msgid "Daily Use"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2176
msgid ""
"This section will explain how to perform common day-to-day operations with "
"Subversion."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2178
#, no-wrap
msgid "Help"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2182
msgid "SVN has built in help documentation.  It can be accessed by typing:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2186
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn help\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2189
msgid ""
"Additional information can be found in the http://svnbook.red-bean.com/"
"[Subversion Book]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2191
#, no-wrap
msgid "Checkout"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2194
msgid "As seen earlier, to check out the FreeBSD head branch:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2202
msgid ""
"At some point, more than just `HEAD` will probably be useful, for instance "
"when merging changes to stable/7.  Therefore, it may be useful to have a "
"partial checkout of the complete tree (a full checkout would be very "
"painful)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2204
msgid "To do this, first check out the root of the repository:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2208
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn checkout --depth=immediates svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/base\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2211
msgid ""
"This will give `base` with all the files it contains (at the time of "
"writing, just [.filename]#ROADMAP.txt#) and empty subdirectories for `head`, "
"`stable`, `vendor` and so on."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2214
msgid ""
"Expanding the working copy is possible.  Just change the depth of the "
"various subdirectories:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2219
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% svn up --set-depth=infinity base/head\n"
"% svn up --set-depth=immediates base/release base/releng base/stable\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2222
msgid ""
"The above command will pull down a full copy of `head`, plus empty copies of "
"every `release` tag, every `releng` branch, and every `stable` branch."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2224
msgid ""
"If at a later date merging to `7-STABLE` is required, expand the working "
"copy:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2228
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn up --set-depth=infinity base/stable/7\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2232
msgid ""
"Subtrees do not have to be expanded completely.  For instance, expanding "
"only `stable/7/sys` and then later expand the rest of `stable/7`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2237
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% svn up --set-depth=infinity base/stable/7/sys\n"
"% svn up --set-depth=infinity base/stable/7\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2240
msgid ""
"Updating the tree with `svn update` will only update what was previously "
"asked for (in this case, `head` and `stable/7`; it will not pull down the "
"whole tree."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2242
#, no-wrap
msgid "Anonymous Checkout"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2247
msgid ""
"It is possible to anonymously check out the FreeBSD repository with "
"Subversion.  This will give access to a read-only tree that can be updated, "
"but not committed back to the main repository.  To do this, use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2251
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn co https://svn.FreeBSD.org/base/head /usr/src\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2254
msgid ""
"More details on using Subversion this way can be found in link:{handbook}"
"#svn[Using Subversion]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2256
#, no-wrap
msgid "Updating the Tree"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2259
msgid ""
"To update a working copy to either the latest revision, or a specific "
"revision:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2264
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% svn update\n"
"% svn update -r12345\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2267
#, no-wrap
msgid "Status"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2270
msgid "To view the local changes that have been made to the working copy:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2274
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn status\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2277
msgid "To show local changes and files that are out-of-date do:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2281
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn status --show-updates\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2284
#, no-wrap
msgid "Editing and Committing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2287
msgid "SVN does not need to be told in advance about file editing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2289
msgid "To commit all changes in the current directory and all subdirectories:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2293
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn commit\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2296
msgid ""
"To commit all changes in, for example, [.filename]#lib/libfetch/# and [."
"filename]#usr/bin/fetch/# in a single operation:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2300
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn commit lib/libfetch usr/bin/fetch\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2303
msgid ""
"There is also a commit wrapper for the ports tree to handle the properties "
"and sanity checking the changes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2307
#, no-wrap
msgid "% /usr/ports/Tools/scripts/psvn commit\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2310
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding and Removing Files"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2317
msgid ""
"Before adding files, get a copy of https://people.FreeBSD.org/~peter/auto-"
"props.txt[auto-props.txt] (there is also a https://people.FreeBSD.org/~beat/"
"cvs2svn/auto-props.txt[ports tree specific version]) and add it to [."
"filename]#~/.subversion/config# according to the instructions in the file.  "
"If you added something before reading this, use `svn rm --keep-local` for "
"just added files, fix your config file and re-add them again.  The initial "
"config file is created when you first run a svn command, even something as "
"simple as `svn help`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2321
msgid ""
"Files are added to a SVN repository with `svn add`.  To add a file named "
"__foo__, edit it, then:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2325
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn add foo\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2332
msgid ""
"Most new source files should include a `$FreeBSD$` string near the start of "
"the file.  On commit, `svn` will expand the `$FreeBSD$` string, adding the "
"file path, revision number, date and time of commit, and the username of the "
"committer.  Files which cannot be modified may be committed without the `"
"$FreeBSD$` string."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2335
msgid "Files can be removed with `svn remove`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2339
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn remove foo\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2342
msgid ""
"Subversion does not require deleting the file before using `svn rm`, and "
"indeed complains if that happens."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2344
msgid "It is possible to add directories with `svn add`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2349
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% mkdir bar\n"
"% svn add bar\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2352
msgid ""
"Although `svn mkdir` makes this easier by combining the creation of the "
"directory and the adding of it:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2356
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn mkdir bar\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2360
msgid ""
"Like files, directories are removed with `svn rm`.  There is no separate "
"command specifically for removing directories."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2364
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn rm bar\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2367
#, no-wrap
msgid "Copying and Moving Files"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2370
msgid ""
"This command creates a copy of [.filename]#foo.c# named [.filename]#bar.c#, "
"with the new file also under version control and with the full history of [."
"filename]#foo.c#:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2374
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn copy foo.c bar.c\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2377
msgid ""
"This is usually preferred to copying the file with `cp` and adding it to the "
"repository with `svn add` because this way the new file does not inherit the "
"original one's history."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2379
msgid "To move and rename a file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2383
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn move foo.c bar.c\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2386
#, no-wrap
msgid "Log and Annotate"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2390
msgid ""
"`svn log` shows revisions and commit messages, most recent first, for files "
"or directories.  When used on a directory, all revisions that affected the "
"directory and files within that directory are shown."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2392
msgid ""
"`svn annotate`, or equally `svn praise` or `svn blame`, shows the most "
"recent revision number and who committed that revision for each line of a "
"file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2394
#, no-wrap
msgid "Diffs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2398
msgid ""
"`svn diff` displays changes to the working copy.  Diffs generated by SVN are "
"unified and include new files by default in the diff output."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2400
msgid "`svn diff` can show the changes between two revisions of the same file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2404
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn diff -r179453:179454 ROADMAP.txt\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2408
msgid ""
"It can also show all changes for a specific changeset.  This command shows "
"what changes were made to the current directory and all subdirectories in "
"changeset 179454:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2412
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn diff -c179454 .\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2415
#, no-wrap
msgid "Reverting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2419
msgid ""
"Local changes (including additions and deletions) can be reverted using `svn "
"revert`.  It does not update out-of-date files, but just replaces them with "
"pristine copies of the original version."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2421
#, no-wrap
msgid "Conflicts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2425
msgid ""
"If an `svn update` resulted in a merge conflict, Subversion will remember "
"which files have conflicts and refuse to commit any changes to those files "
"until explicitly told that the conflicts have been resolved.  The simple, "
"not yet deprecated procedure is:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2429
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn resolved foo\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2432
msgid "However, the preferred procedure is:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2436
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn resolve --accept=working foo\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2440
msgid "The two examples are equivalent.  Possible values for `--accept` are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2442
msgid ""
"`working`: use the version in your working directory (which one presumes has "
"been edited to resolve the conflicts)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2443
msgid ""
"`base`: use a pristine copy of the version you had before `svn update`, "
"discarding your own changes, the conflicting changes, and possibly other "
"intervening changes as well."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2444
msgid ""
"`mine-full`: use what you had before `svn update`, including your own "
"changes, but discarding the conflicting changes, and possibly other "
"intervening changes as well."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2445
msgid ""
"`theirs-full`: use the version that was retrieved when you did `svn update`, "
"discarding your own changes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2446
#, no-wrap
msgid "Advanced Use"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2449
#, no-wrap
msgid "Sparse Checkouts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2452
msgid ""
"SVN allows __sparse__, or partial checkouts of a directory by adding `--"
"depth` to a `svn checkout`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2454
msgid "Valid arguments to `--depth` are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2456
msgid "`empty`: the directory itself without any of its contents."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2457
msgid "`files`: the directory and any files it contains."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2458
msgid ""
"`immediates`: the directory and any files and directories it contains, but "
"none of the subdirectories' contents."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2459
msgid "`infinity`: anything."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2461
msgid ""
"The `--depth` option applies to many other commands, including `svn commit`, "
"`svn revert`, and `svn diff`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2464
msgid ""
"Since `--depth` is sticky, there is a `--set-depth` option for `svn update` "
"that will change the selected depth.  Thus, given the working copy produced "
"by the previous example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2469
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% cd ~/freebsd\n"
"% svn update --set-depth=immediates .\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2473
msgid ""
"The above command will populate the working copy in _~/freebsd_ with [."
"filename]#ROADMAP.txt# and empty subdirectories, and nothing will happen "
"when `svn update` is executed on the subdirectories.  However, this command "
"will set the depth for _head_ (in this case) to infinity, and fully populate "
"it:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2477
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn update --set-depth=infinity head\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2480
#, no-wrap
msgid "Direct Operation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2484
msgid ""
"Certain operations can be performed directly on the repository without "
"touching the working copy.  Specifically, this applies to any operation that "
"does not require editing a file, including:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2486
msgid "`log`, `diff`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2487
msgid "`mkdir`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2488
msgid "`remove`, `copy`, `rename`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2489
msgid "`propset`, `propedit`, `propdel`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2490
msgid "`merge`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2493
msgid ""
"Branching is very fast.  This command would be used to branch `RELENG_8`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2497
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn copy svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/base/head svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/base/stable/8\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2500
msgid ""
"This is equivalent to these commands which take minutes and hours as opposed "
"to seconds, depending on your network connection:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2508
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% svn checkout --depth=immediates svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/base\n"
"% cd base\n"
"% svn update --set-depth=infinity head\n"
"% svn copy head stable/8\n"
"% svn commit stable/8\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2511
#, no-wrap
msgid "Merging with SVN"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2514
msgid ""
"This section deals with merging code from one branch to another (typically, "
"from head to a stable branch)."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2518
msgid ""
"In all examples below, `$FSVN` refers to the location of the FreeBSD "
"Subversion repository, `svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/base/`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2520
#, no-wrap
msgid "About Merge Tracking"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2525
msgid ""
"From the user's perspective, merge tracking information (or mergeinfo) is "
"stored in a property called `svn:mergeinfo`, which is a comma-separated list "
"of revisions and ranges of revisions that have been merged.  When set on a "
"file, it applies only to that file.  When set on a directory, it applies to "
"that directory and its descendants (files and directories) except for those "
"that have their own `svn:mergeinfo`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2530
msgid ""
"It is _not_ inherited.  For instance, [.filename]#stable/6/contrib/openpam/# "
"does not implicitly inherit mergeinfo from [.filename]#stable/6/#, or [."
"filename]#stable/6/contrib/#. Doing so would make partial checkouts very "
"hard to manage.  Instead, mergeinfo is explicitly propagated down the tree.  "
"For merging something into [.filename]#branch/foo/bar/#, these rules apply:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2532
msgid ""
"If [.filename]#branch/foo/bar/# does not already have a mergeinfo record, "
"but a direct ancestor (for instance, [.filename]#branch/foo/#) does, then "
"that record will be propagated down to [.filename]#branch/foo/bar/# before "
"information about the current merge is recorded."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2533
msgid ""
"Information about the current merge will _not_ be propagated back up that "
"ancestor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2534
msgid ""
"If a direct descendant of [.filename]#branch/foo/bar/# (for instance, [."
"filename]#branch/foo/bar/baz/#) already has a mergeinfo record, information "
"about the current merge will be propagated down to it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2537
msgid ""
"If you consider the case where a revision changes several separate parts of "
"the tree (for example, [.filename]#branch/foo/bar/# and [.filename]#branch/"
"foo/quux/#), but you only want to merge some of it (for example, [."
"filename]#branch/foo/bar/#), you will see that these rules make sense.  If "
"mergeinfo was propagated up, it would seem like that revision had also been "
"merged to [.filename]#branch/foo/quux/#, when in fact it had not been."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2539
#, no-wrap
msgid "Selecting the Source and Target Branch When Merging"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2542
msgid ""
"Merging to `stable/` branches should originate from `head/`. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2547
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% svn merge -c r123456 ^/head/ stable/11\n"
"% svn commit stable/11\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2551
msgid ""
"Merges to `releng/` branches should always originate from the corresponding "
"`stable/` branch.  For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2556
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% svn merge -c r123456 ^/stable/11  releng/11.0\n"
"% svn commit releng/11.0\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2561
msgid ""
"Committers are only permitted to commit to the `releng/` branches during a "
"release cycle after receiving approval from the Release Engineering Team, "
"after which only the Security Officer may commit to a `releng/` branch for a "
"Security Advisory or Errata Notice."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2564
msgid ""
"All merges are merged to and committed from the root of the branch. All "
"merges look like:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2569
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% svn merge -c r123456 ^/head/ checkout\n"
"% svn commit checkout\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2572
msgid ""
"Note that _checkout_ must be a complete checkout of the branch to which the "
"merge occurs."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2576
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn merge -c r123456 ^/stable/10 releng/10.0\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2578
#, no-wrap
msgid "Preparing the Merge Target"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2583
msgid ""
"Due to the mergeinfo propagation issues described earlier, it is very "
"important to never merge changes into a sparse working copy.  Always use a "
"full checkout of the branch being merged into.  For instance, when merging "
"from HEAD to 7, use a full checkout of stable/7:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2588
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% cd stable/7\n"
"% svn up --set-depth=infinity\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2591
msgid ""
"The target directory must also be up-to-date and must not contain any "
"uncommitted changes or stray files."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2592
#, no-wrap
msgid "Identifying Revisions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2596
msgid ""
"Identifying revisions to be merged is a must.  If the target already has "
"complete mergeinfo, ask SVN for a list:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2601
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% cd stable/6/contrib/openpam\n"
"% svn mergeinfo --show-revs=eligible $FSVN/head/contrib/openpam\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2604
msgid ""
"If the target does not have complete mergeinfo, check the log for the merge "
"source."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2605
#, no-wrap
msgid "Merging"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2608
msgid "Now, let us start merging!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2610
msgid "====== The Principles"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2612
msgid "For example, To merge:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2614
msgid "revision `$R`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2615
msgid "in directory $target in stable branch $B"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2616
msgid "from directory $source in head"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2617
msgid "$FSVN is `svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/base`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2619
msgid ""
"Assuming that revisions $P and $Q have already been merged, and that the "
"current directory is an up-to-date working copy of stable/$B, the existing "
"mergeinfo looks like this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2624
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% svn propget svn:mergeinfo -R $target\n"
"$target - /head/$source:$P,$Q\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2627
msgid "Merging is done like so:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2631
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn merge -c$R $FSVN/head/$source $target\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2634
msgid "Checking the results of this is possible with `svn diff`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2636
msgid "The svn:mergeinfo now looks like:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2641
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% svn propget svn:mergeinfo -R $target\n"
"$target - head/$source:$P,$Q,$R\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2644
msgid ""
"If the results are not exactly as shown, assistance may be required before "
"committing as mistakes may have been made, or there may be something wrong "
"with the existing mergeinfo, or there may be a bug in Subversion."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2646
msgid "====== Practical Example"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2652
msgid ""
"As a practical example, consider this scenario.  The changes to [."
"filename]#netmap.4# in r238987 are to be merged from CURRENT to 9-STABLE.  "
"The file resides in [.filename]#head/shared/man/man4#. According to <<svn-"
"advanced-use-merging>>, this is also where to do the merge.  Note that in "
"this example all paths are relative to the top of the svn repository.  For "
"more information on the directory layout, see <<svn-getting-started-base-"
"layout>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2654
msgid "The first step is to inspect the existing mergeinfo."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2658
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn propget svn:mergeinfo -R stable/9/shared/man/man4\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2661
msgid ""
"Take a quick note of how it looks before moving on to the next step; doing "
"the actual merge:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2670
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% svn merge -c r238987 svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/base/head/shared/man/man4 stable/9/shared/man/man4\n"
"--- Merging r238987 into 'stable/9/shared/man/man4':\n"
"U    stable/9/shared/man/man4/netmap.4\n"
"--- Recording mergeinfo for merge of r238987 into\n"
"'stable/9/shared/man/man4':\n"
" U   stable/9/shared/man/man4\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2674
msgid ""
"Check that the revision number of the merged revision has been added.  Once "
"this is verified, the only thing left is the actual commit."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2678
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn commit stable/9/shared/man/man4\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2680
#, no-wrap
msgid "Precautions Before Committing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2683
msgid "As always, build world (or appropriate parts of it)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2686
msgid ""
"Check the changes with svn diff and `svn stat`.  Make sure all the files "
"that should have been added or deleted were in fact added or deleted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2689
msgid ""
"Take a closer look at any property change (marked by a `M` in the second "
"column of `svn stat`).  Normally, no svn:mergeinfo properties should be "
"anywhere except the target directory (or directories)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2691
msgid "If something looks fishy, ask for help."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2692
#, no-wrap
msgid "Committing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2697
msgid ""
"Make sure to commit a top level directory to have the mergeinfo included as "
"well.  Do not specify individual files on the command line.  For more "
"information about committing files in general, see the relevant section of "
"this primer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2699
#, no-wrap
msgid "Reverting a Commit"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2702
msgid "Reverting a commit to a previous version is fairly easy:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2707
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% svn merge -r179454:179453 ROADMAP.txt\n"
"% svn commit\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2710
msgid ""
"Change number syntax, with negative meaning a reverse change, can also be "
"used:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2715
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% svn merge -c -179454 ROADMAP.txt\n"
"% svn commit\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2718
msgid "This can also be done directly in the repository:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2722
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn merge -r179454:179453 svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/base/ROADMAP.txt\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2727
msgid ""
"It is important to ensure that the mergeinfo is correct when reverting a "
"file to permit `svn mergeinfo --eligible` to work as expected."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2732
msgid ""
"Reverting the deletion of a file is slightly different.  Copying the version "
"of the file that predates the deletion is required.  For example, to restore "
"a file that was deleted in revision N, restore version N-1:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2737
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% svn copy svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/base/ROADMAP.txt@179454\n"
"% svn commit\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2740
msgid "or, equally:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2744
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn copy svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/base/ROADMAP.txt@179454 svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/base\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2747
msgid ""
"Do _not_ simply recreate the file manually and `svn add` it-this will cause "
"history to be lost."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2749
#, no-wrap
msgid "Fixing Mistakes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2754
msgid ""
"While we can do surgery in an emergency, do not plan on having mistakes "
"fixed behind the scenes.  Plan on mistakes remaining in the logs forever.  "
"Be sure to check the output of `svn status` and `svn diff` before committing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2756
msgid ""
"Mistakes will happen but, they can generally be fixed without disruption."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2760
msgid ""
"Take a case of adding a file in the wrong location.  The right thing to do "
"is to `svn move` the file to the correct location and commit.  This causes "
"just a couple of lines of metadata in the repository journal, and the logs "
"are all linked up correctly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2764
msgid ""
"The wrong thing to do is to delete the file and then `svn add` an "
"independent copy in the correct location.  Instead of a couple of lines of "
"text, the repository journal grows an entire new copy of the file.  This is "
"a waste."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2766
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using a Subversion Mirror"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2770
msgid ""
"There is a serious disadvantage to this method: every time something is to "
"be committed, a `svn relocate` to the main repository has to be done, "
"remembering to `svn relocate` back to the mirror after the commit.  Also, "
"since `svn relocate` only works between repositories that have the same "
"UUID, some hacking of the local repository's UUID has to occur before it is "
"possible to start using it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2772
#, no-wrap
msgid "Checkout from a Mirror"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2776
msgid ""
"Check out a working copy from a mirror by substituting the mirror's URL for "
"`svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/base`.  This can be an official mirror or a "
"mirror maintained by using `svnsync`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2778
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting up a svnsync Mirror"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2785
msgid ""
"Avoid setting up a svnsync mirror unless there is a very good reason for "
"it.  Most of the time a `git` mirror is a better alternative.  Starting a "
"fresh mirror from scratch takes a long time.  Expect a minimum of 10 hours "
"for high speed connectivity.  If international links are involved, expect "
"this to take four to ten times longer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2788
msgid ""
"One way to limit the time required is to grab a https://download.freebsd.org/"
"ftp/development/subversion/[seed file].  It is large (~1GB) but will consume "
"less network traffic and take less time to fetch than svnsync will."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2790
msgid "Extract the file and update it:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2795
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% tar xf svnmirror-base-r261170.tar.xz\n"
"% svnsync sync file:///home/svnmirror/base\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2798
msgid ""
"Now, set that up to run from man:cron[8], do checkouts locally, set up a "
"svnserve server for local machines to talk to, etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2802
msgid ""
"The seed mirror is set to fetch from `svn://svn.freebsd.org/base`.  The "
"configuration for the mirror is stored in `revprop 0` on the local mirror.  "
"To see the configuration, try:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2806
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn proplist -v --revprop -r 0 file:///home/svnmirror/base\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2809
msgid "Use `svn propset` to change things."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2811
#, no-wrap
msgid "Committing High-ASCII Data"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2816
msgid ""
"Files that have high-ASCII bits are considered binary files in SVN, so the "
"pre-commit checks fail and indicate that the `mime-type` property should be "
"set to `application/octet-stream`.  However, the use of this is discouraged, "
"so please do not set it.  The best way is always avoiding high-ASCII data, "
"so that it can be read everywhere with any text editor but if it is not "
"avoidable, instead of changing the mime-type, set the `fbsd:notbinary` "
"property with `propset`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2820
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn propset fbsd:notbinary yes foo.data\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2823
#, no-wrap
msgid "Maintaining a Project Branch"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2831
msgid ""
"A project branch is one that is synced to head (or another branch) is used "
"to develop a project then commit it back to head.  In SVN, \"dolphin\" "
"branching is used for this.  A \"dolphin\" branch is one that diverges for a "
"while and is finally committed back to the original branch.  During "
"development code migration in one direction (from head to the branch only).  "
"No code is committed back to head until the end.  After the branch is "
"committed back at the end, it is dead (although a new branch with the same "
"name can be created after the dead one is deleted)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2835
msgid ""
"As per https://people.FreeBSD.org/\\~peter/svn_notes.txt[https://people."
"FreeBSD.org/~peter/svn_notes.txt], work that is intended to be merged back "
"into HEAD should be in [.filename]#base/projects/#.  If the work is "
"beneficial to the FreeBSD community in some way but not intended to be "
"merged directly back into HEAD then the proper location is [.filename]#base/"
"user/username/#.  https://svnweb.freebsd.org/base/projects/GUIDELINES."
"txt[This page] contains further details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2837
msgid "To create a project branch:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2841
#, no-wrap
msgid "% svn copy svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/base/head svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/base/projects/spif\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2844
msgid "To merge changes from HEAD back into the project branch:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2850
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% cd copy_of_spif\n"
"% svn merge svn+ssh://repo.freebsd.org/base/head\n"
"% svn commit\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2853
msgid "It is important to resolve any merge conflicts before committing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2854
#, no-wrap
msgid "Some Tips"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2857
msgid ""
"In commit logs etc., \"rev 179872\" is spelled \"r179872\" as per convention."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2859
msgid ""
"Speeding up svn is possible by adding these entries to [.filename]#~/.ssh/"
"config#:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2866
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Host *\n"
"ControlPath ~/.ssh/sockets/master-l-r@h:p\n"
"ControlMaster auto\n"
"ControlPersist yes\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2869
msgid "and then typing"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2873
#, no-wrap
msgid " mkdir ~/.ssh/sockets\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2877
msgid ""
"Checking out a working copy with a stock Subversion client without FreeBSD-"
"specific patches (`OPTIONS_SET=FREEBSD_TEMPLATE`) will mean that `$FreeBSD$` "
"tags will not be expanded.  Once the correct version has been installed, "
"trick Subversion into expanding them like so:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2882
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% svn propdel -R svn:keywords .\n"
"% svn revert -R .\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2885
msgid "This will wipe out uncommitted patches."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2888
msgid ""
"It is possible to automatically fill the \"Sponsored by\" and \"MFC after\" "
"commit log fields by setting \"freebsd-sponsored-by\" and \"freebsd-mfc-after"
"\" fields in the \"[miscellany]\" section of the [.filename]#~/.subversion/"
"config# configuration file.  For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2893
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"freebsd-sponsored-by = The FreeBSD Foundation\n"
"freebsd-mfc-after = 2 weeks\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2896
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setup, Conventions, and Traditions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2901
msgid ""
"There are a number of things to do as a new developer.  The first set of "
"steps is specific to committers only.  These steps must be done by a mentor "
"for those who are not committers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2903
#, no-wrap
msgid "For New Committers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2906
msgid ""
"Those who have been given commit rights to the FreeBSD repositories must "
"follow these steps."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2908
msgid "Get mentor approval before committing each of these changes!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2909
msgid ""
"The [.filename]#.ent# and [.filename]#.xml# files mentioned below exist in "
"the FreeBSD Documentation Project SVN repository at `svn+ssh://repo.FreeBSD."
"org/doc/`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2910
msgid ""
"New files that do not have the `FreeBSD=%H svn:keywords` property will be "
"rejected when attempting to commit them to the repository. Be sure to read "
"<<svn-daily-use-adding-and-removing>> regarding adding and removing files. "
"Verify that [.filename]#~/.subversion/config# contains the necessary \"auto-"
"props\" entries from [.filename]#auto-props.txt# mentioned there."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2911
msgid ""
"All [.filename]#src# commits go to FreeBSD-CURRENT first before being merged "
"to FreeBSD-STABLE. The FreeBSD-STABLE branch must maintain ABI and API "
"compatibility with earlier versions of that branch. Do not merge changes "
"that break this compatibility."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2916
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Procedure 1. Steps for New Committers*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2918
msgid "Add an Author Entity"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2920
msgid ""
"  [.filename]#shared/authors.toml# - Add an author entity. Later steps "
"depend on this entity, and missing this step will cause the [.filename]#doc/"
"# build to fail. This is a relatively easy task, but remains a good first "
"test of version control skills."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2921
msgid "Update the List of Developers and Contributors"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2923
msgid ""
"  [.filename]#doc/en/articles/contributors/contrib-committers.adoc# - Add an "
"entry to the \"Developers\" section of the link:{contributors}#staff-"
"committers[Contributors List]. Entries are sorted by last name."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2925
msgid ""
"  [.filename]#doc/en/articles/contributors/contrib-additional.adoc# - "
"_Remove_ the entry from the \"Additional Contributors\" section. Entries are "
"sorted by first name."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2926
msgid "Add a News Item"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2928
msgid ""
"  [.filename]#website/data/en/news/news.toml# - Add an entry. Look for the "
"other entries that announce new committers and follow the format. Use the "
"date from the commit bit approval email from mailto:core@FreeBSD."
"org[core@FreeBSD.org]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2929
msgid "Add a PGP Key"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2931
msgid ""
"  `{des}` has written a shell script ([.filename]#documentation/tools/addkey."
"sh#) to make this easier. See the http://svnweb.FreeBSD.org/doc/head/shared/"
"pgpkeys/README[README] file for more information."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2933
msgid ""
"  Use [.filename]#documentation/tools/checkkey.sh# to verify that keys meet "
"minimal best-practices standards."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2935
msgid ""
"  After adding and checking a key, add both updated files to source control "
"and then commit them. Entries in this file are sorted by last name."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 6
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2939
msgid ""
"It is very important to have a current PGP/GnuPG key in the repository. The "
"key may be required for positive identification of a committer. For example, "
"the `{admins}` might need it for account recovery. A complete keyring of "
"`FreeBSD.org` users is available for download from link:https://www.FreeBSD."
"org/doc/pgpkeyring.txt[https://www.FreeBSD.org/doc/pgpkeyring.txt]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2941
msgid "Update Mentor and Mentee Information"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2943
msgid ""
"  [.filename]#base/head/shared/misc/committers-repository.dot# - Add an "
"entry to the current committers section, where _repository_ is `doc`, "
"`ports`, or `src`, depending on the commit privileges granted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2945
msgid ""
"  Add an entry for each additional mentor/mentee relationship in the bottom "
"section."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2946
msgid "Generate a Kerberos Password"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2948
msgid ""
"  See <<kerberos-ldap>> to generate or set a Kerberos for use with other "
"FreeBSD services like the bug tracking database."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2949
msgid "Optional: Enable Wiki Account"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2951
msgid ""
"  https://wiki.freebsd.org[FreeBSD Wiki] Account - A wiki account allows "
"sharing projects and ideas. Those who do not yet have an account can follow "
"instructions on the https://wiki.freebsd.org/AboutWiki[AboutWiki Page] to "
"obtain one. Contact mailto:wiki-admin@FreeBSD.org[wiki-admin@FreeBSD.org] if "
"you need help with your Wiki account."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2952
msgid "Optional: Update Wiki Information"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2954
msgid ""
"  Wiki Information - After gaining access to the wiki, some people add "
"entries to the https://wiki.freebsd.org/HowWeGotHere[How We Got Here], "
"https://wiki.freebsd.org/IRC/Nicknames[IRC Nicks], and https://wiki.freebsd."
"org/Community/Dogs[Dogs of FreeBSD] pages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2955
msgid "Optional: Update Ports with Personal Information"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2957
msgid ""
"  [.filename]#ports/astro/xearth/files/freebsd.committers.markers# and [."
"filename]#src/usr.bin/calendar/calendars/calendar.freebsd# - Some people add "
"entries for themselves to these files to show where they are located or the "
"date of their birthday."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2958
msgid "Optional: Prevent Duplicate Mailings"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2960
msgid ""
"  Subscribers to {dev-commits-doc-all}, {dev-commits-ports-all} or {dev-"
"commits-src-all} might wish to unsubscribe to avoid receiving duplicate "
"copies of commit messages and followups."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2963
#, no-wrap
msgid "For Everyone"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2969
msgid ""
"Introduce yourself to the other developers, otherwise no one will have any "
"idea who you are or what you are working on. The introduction need not be a "
"comprehensive biography, just write a paragraph or two about who you are, "
"what you plan to be working on as a developer in FreeBSD, and who will be "
"your mentor. Email this to the {developers-name} and you will be on your way!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2970
msgid ""
"Log into `freefall.FreeBSD.org` and create a [.filename]#/var/forward/user# "
"(where _user_ is your username) file containing the e-mail address where you "
"want mail addressed to _yourusername_@FreeBSD.org to be forwarded. This "
"includes all of the commit messages as well as any other mail addressed to "
"the {committers-name} and the {developers-name}. Really large mailboxes "
"which have taken up permanent residence on `freefall` may get truncated "
"without warning if space needs to be freed, so forward it or save it "
"elsewhere."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 6
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2974
msgid ""
"If your e-mail system uses SPF with strict rules, you should whitelist `mx2."
"FreeBSD.org` from SPF checks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2977
msgid ""
"  Due to the severe load dealing with SPAM places on the central mail "
"servers that do the mailing list processing, the front-end server does do "
"some basic checks and will drop some messages based on these checks. At the "
"moment proper DNS information for the connecting host is the only check in "
"place but that may change. Some people blame these checks for bouncing valid "
"email. To have these checks turned off for your email, create a file named [."
"filename]#~/.spam_lover# on `freefall.FreeBSD.org`."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 6
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2981
msgid ""
"Those who are developers but not committers will not be subscribed to the "
"committers or developers mailing lists. The subscriptions are derived from "
"the access rights."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2985
#, no-wrap
msgid "SMTP Access Setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2988
msgid ""
"For those willing to send e-mail messages through the FreeBSD.org "
"infrastructure, follow the instructions below:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2992
msgid "Point your mail client at `smtp.FreeBSD.org:587`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2993
msgid "Enable STARTTLS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2994
msgid "Ensure your `From:` address is set to `_yourusername_@FreeBSD.org`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2995
msgid ""
"For authentication, you can use your FreeBSD Kerberos username and password "
"(see <<kerberos-ldap>>). The `_yourusername_/mail` principal is preferred, "
"as it is only valid for authenticating to mail resources."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 6
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:2999
msgid "Do not include `@FreeBSD.org` when entering in your username."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3001
#, no-wrap
msgid "Additional Notes"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 6
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3005
msgid ""
"Will only accept mail from `_yourusername_@FreeBSD.org`. If you are "
"authenticated as one user, you are not permitted to send mail from another."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 6
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3006
msgid ""
"A header will be appended with the SASL username: (`Authenticated sender: "
"_username_`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 6
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3007
msgid ""
"Host has various rate limits in place to cut down on brute force attempts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3011
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using a Local MTA to Forward Emails to the FreeBSD.org SMTP Service"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3014
msgid ""
"It is also possible to use a local MTA to forward locally sent emails to the "
"FreeBSD.org SMTP servers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3016
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using Postfix"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3021
msgid ""
"To tell a local Postfix instance that anything from `_yourusername_@FreeBSD."
"org` should be forwarded to the FreeBSD.org servers, add this to your [."
"filename]#main.cf#:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3029
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"sender_dependent_relayhost_maps = hash:/usr/local/etc/postfix/relayhost_maps\n"
"smtp_sasl_auth_enable = yes\n"
"smtp_sasl_security_options = noanonymous\n"
"smtp_sasl_password_maps = hash:/usr/local/etc/postfix/sasl_passwd\n"
"smtp_use_tls = yes\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3032
msgid ""
"Create [.filename]#/usr/local/etc/postfix/relayhost_maps# with the following "
"content:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3036
#, no-wrap
msgid "yourusername@FreeBSD.org  [smtp.freebsd.org]:587\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3039
msgid ""
"Create [.filename]#/usr/local/etc/postfix/sasl_passwd# with the following "
"content:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3043
#, no-wrap
msgid "[smtp.freebsd.org]:587          yourusername:yourpassword\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3046
msgid ""
"If the email server is used by other people, you may want to prevent them "
"from sending e-mails from your address. To achieve this, add this to your [."
"filename]#main.cf#:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3051
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"smtpd_sender_login_maps = hash:/usr/local/etc/postfix/sender_login_maps\n"
"smtpd_sender_restrictions = reject_known_sender_login_mismatch\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3054
msgid ""
"Create [.filename]#/usr/local/etc/postfix/sender_login_maps# with the "
"following content:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3058
#, no-wrap
msgid "yourusername@FreeBSD.org yourlocalusername\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3061
msgid ""
"Where _yourlocalusername_ is the SASL username used to connect to the local "
"instance of Postfix."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3064
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mentors"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3069
msgid ""
"All new developers have a mentor assigned to them for the first few months.  "
"A mentor is responsible for teaching the mentee the rules and conventions of "
"the project and guiding their first steps in the developer community.  The "
"mentor is also personally responsible for the mentee's actions during this "
"initial period."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3072
msgid ""
"For committers: do not commit anything without first getting mentor "
"approval.  Document that approval with an `Approved by:` line in the commit "
"message."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3075
msgid ""
"When the mentor decides that a mentee has learned the ropes and is ready to "
"commit on their own, the mentor announces it with a commit to [."
"filename]#conf/mentors#.  This file is in the [.filename]#svnadmin# branch "
"of each repository:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3088
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"|`src`\n"
"|[.filename]#base/svnadmin/conf/mentors#\n"
"\n"
"|`doc`\n"
"|[.filename]#doc/svnadmin/conf/mentors#\n"
"\n"
"|`ports`\n"
"|[.filename]#ports/svnadmin/conf/mentors#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3091
#, no-wrap
msgid "Pre-Commit Review"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3096
msgid ""
"Code review is one way to increase the quality of software.  The following "
"guidelines apply to commits to the `head` (-CURRENT) branch of the `src` "
"repository.  Other branches and the `ports` and `docs` trees have their own "
"review policies, but these guidelines generally apply to commits requiring "
"review:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3098
msgid ""
"All non-trivial changes should be reviewed before they are committed to the "
"repository."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3099
msgid ""
"Reviews may be conducted by email, in Bugzilla, in Phabricator, or by "
"another mechanism. Where possible, reviews should be public."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3100
msgid ""
"The developer responsible for a code change is also responsible for making "
"all necessary review-related changes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3101
msgid ""
"Code review can be an iterative process, which continues until the patch is "
"ready to be committed. Specifically, once a patch is sent out for review, it "
"should receive an explicit \"looks good\" before it is committed. So long as "
"it is explicit, this can take whatever form makes sense for the review "
"method."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3102
msgid "Timeouts are not a substitute for review."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3104
msgid ""
"Sometimes code reviews will take longer than you would hope for, especially "
"for larger features. Accepted ways to speed up review times for your patches "
"are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3106
msgid ""
"Review other people's patches. If you help out, everybody will be more "
"willing to do the same for you; goodwill is our currency."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3107
msgid ""
"Ping the patch. If it is urgent, provide reasons why it is important to you "
"to get this patch landed and ping it every couple of days. If it is not "
"urgent, the common courtesy ping rate is one week. Remember that you are "
"asking for valuable time from other professional developers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3108
msgid ""
"Ask for help on mailing lists, IRC, etc. Others may be able to either help "
"you directly, or suggest a reviewer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3109
msgid ""
"Split your patch into multiple smaller patches that build on each other. The "
"smaller your patch, the higher the probability that somebody will take a "
"quick look at it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3111
msgid ""
"  When making large changes, it is helpful to keep this in mind from the "
"beginning of the effort as breaking large changes into smaller ones is often "
"difficult after the fact."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3116
msgid ""
"Developers should participate in code reviews as both reviewers and "
"reviewees.  If someone is kind enough to review your code, you should return "
"the favor for someone else.  Note that while anyone is welcome to review and "
"give feedback on a patch, only an appropriate subject-matter expert can "
"approve a change.  This will usually be a committer who works with the code "
"in question on a regular basis."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3119
msgid ""
"In some cases, no subject-matter expert may be available.  In those cases, a "
"review by an experienced developer is sufficient when coupled with "
"appropriate testing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3121
#, no-wrap
msgid "Commit Log Messages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3124
msgid ""
"This section contains some suggestions and traditions for how commit logs "
"are formatted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3125
#, no-wrap
msgid "Why are commit messages important?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3129
msgid ""
"When you commit a change in Git, Subversion, or another version control "
"system (VCS), you're prompted to write some text describing the commit -- a "
"commit message.  How important is this commit message? Should you spend some "
"significant effort writing it? Does it really matter if you write simply "
"fixed a bug?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3132
msgid ""
"Most projects have more than one developer and last for some length of "
"time.  Commit messages are a very important method of communicating with "
"other developers, in the present and for the future."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3135
msgid ""
"FreeBSD has hundreds of active developers and hundreds of thousands of "
"commits spanning decades of history.  Over that time the developer community "
"has learned how valuable good commit messages are; sometimes these are hard-"
"learned lessons."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3137
msgid "Commit messages serve at least three purposes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3139
msgid "Communicating with other developers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3144
msgid ""
"FreeBSD commits generate email to various mailing lists.  These include the "
"commit message along with a copy of the patch itself.  Commit messages are "
"also viewed through commands like git log.  These serve to make other "
"developers aware of changes that are ongoing; that other developer may want "
"to test the change, may have an interest in the topic and will want to "
"review in more detail, or may have their own projects underway that would "
"benefit from interaction."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3146
msgid "Making Changes Discoverable"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3150
msgid ""
"In a large project with a long history it may be difficult to find changes "
"of interest when investigating an issue or change in behaviour.  Verbose, "
"detailed commit messages allow searches for changes that might be relevant.  "
"For example, `git log --since 1year --grep 'USB timeout'`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3152
msgid "Providing historical documentation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3156
msgid ""
"Commit messages serve to document changes for future developers, perhaps "
"years or decades later.  This future developer may even be you, the original "
"author.  A change that seems obvious today may be decidedly not so much "
"later on."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3158
msgid ""
"The `git blame` command annotates each line of a source file with the change "
"(hash and subject line) that brought it in."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3160
msgid ""
"Having established the importance, here are elements of a good FreeBSD "
"commit message:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3161
#, no-wrap
msgid "Start with a subject line"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3165
msgid ""
"Commit messages should start with a single-line subject that briefly "
"summarizes the change.  The subject should, by itself, allow the reader to "
"quickly determine if the change is of interest or not."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3166
#, no-wrap
msgid "Keep subject lines short"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3171
msgid ""
"The subject line should be as short as possible while still retaining the "
"required information.  This is to make browsing git log more efficient, and "
"so that git log --oneline can display the short hash and subject on a single "
"80-column line.  A good rule of thumb is to stay below 63 characters, and "
"aim for about 50 or fewer if possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3172
#, no-wrap
msgid "Prefix the subject line with a component, if applicable"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3175
msgid ""
"If the change relates to a specific component the subject line may be "
"prefixed with that component name and a colon (:)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3177
msgid "✓ `foo: Add -k option to keep temporary data`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3179
msgid ""
"Include the prefix in the 63-character limit suggested above, so that `git "
"log --oneline` avoids wrapping."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3180
#, no-wrap
msgid "Capitalize the first letter of the subject"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3184
msgid ""
"Capitalize the first letter of the subject itself.  The prefix, if any, is "
"not capitalized unless necessary (e.g., `USB:` is capitalized)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3185
#, no-wrap
msgid "Do not end the subject line with punctuation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3189
msgid ""
"Do not end with a period or other punctuation.  In this regard the subject "
"line is like a newspaper headline."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3190
#, no-wrap
msgid "Separate the subject and body with a blank line"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3193
msgid "Separate the body from the subject with a blank line."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3195
msgid ""
"Some trivial commits do not require a body, and will have only a subject."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3197
msgid "✓ `ls: Fix typo in usage text`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3198
#, no-wrap
msgid "Limit messages to 72 columns"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3204
msgid ""
"`git log` and `git format-patch` indent the commit message by four spaces.  "
"Wrapping at 72 columns provides a matching margin on the right edge.  "
"Limiting messages to 72 characters also keeps the commit message in "
"formatted patches below RFC 2822's suggested email line length limit of 78 "
"characters.  This limit works well with a variety of tools that may render "
"commit messages; line wrapping might be inconsistent with longer line length."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3205
#, no-wrap
msgid "Use the present tense, imperative mood"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3210
msgid ""
"This facilitates short subject lines and provides consistency, including "
"with automatically generated commit messages (e.g., as generated by git "
"revert).  This is important when reading a list of commit subjects.  Think "
"of the subject as finishing the sentence \"when applied, this change will ..."
"\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3215
msgid ""
"✓ `foo: Implement the -k (keep) option` + ✗ `foo: Implemented the -k option` "
"+ ✗ `This change implements the -k option in foo` + ✗ `-k option added`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3216
#, no-wrap
msgid "Focus on what and why, not how"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3219
msgid ""
"Explain what the change accomplishes and why it is being done, rather than "
"how."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3223
msgid ""
"Do not assume that the reader is familiar with the issue.  Explain the "
"background and motivation for the change.  Include benchmark data if you "
"have it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3225
msgid ""
"If there are limitations or incomplete aspects of the change, describe them "
"in the commit message."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3226
#, no-wrap
msgid "Consider whether parts of the commit message could be code comments instead"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3229
msgid ""
"Sometimes while writing a commit message you may find yourself writing a "
"sentence or two explaining some tricky or confusing aspect of the change. "
"When this happens consider whether it would be valuable to have that "
"explanation as a comment in the code itself."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3230
#, no-wrap
msgid "Write commit messages for your future self"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3234
msgid ""
"While writing the commit message for a change you have all of the context in "
"mind - what prompted the change, alternate approaches that were considered "
"and rejected, limitations of the change, and so on.  Imagine yourself "
"revisiting the change a year or two in the future, and write the commit "
"message in a way that would provide that necessary context."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3235
#, no-wrap
msgid "Commit messages should stand alone"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3239
msgid ""
"You may include references to mailing list postings, benchmark result web "
"sites, or code review links.  However, the commit message should contain all "
"of the relevant information in case these references are no longer available "
"in the future."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3243
msgid ""
"Similarly, a commit may refer to a previous commit, for example in the case "
"of a bug fix or revert.  In addition to the commit identifier (revision or "
"hash), include the subject line from the referenced commit (or another "
"suitable brief reference).  With each VCS migration (from CVS to Subversion "
"to Git) revision identifiers from previous systems may become difficult to "
"follow."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3244
#, no-wrap
msgid "Include appropriate metadata in a footer"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3247
msgid ""
"As well as including an informative message with each commit, some "
"additional information may be needed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3249
msgid ""
"This information consists of one or more lines containing the key word or "
"phrase, a colon, tabs for formatting, and then the additional information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3251
msgid "The key words or phrases are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3287
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"|`PR:`\n"
"|The problem report (if any) which is affected (typically, by being closed) by this commit. Multiple PRs may be specified on one line, separated by commas or spaces.\n"
"\n"
"|`Reported by:`\n"
"|The name and e-mail address of the person that reported the issue; for developers, just the username on the FreeBSD cluster.\n"
"Typically used when there is no PR, for example if the issue was reported on\n"
"a mailing list.\n"
"\n"
"|`Submitted by:`\n"
"|The name and e-mail address of the person that submitted the fix; for developers, just the username on the FreeBSD cluster.\n"
"\n"
"Typically not used with git; in the src and doc trees submitted patches should\n"
"have the author set by using `git commit --author`\n"
"\n"
"If the submitter is the maintainer of the port being committed, include \"(maintainer)\" after the email address.\n"
"\n"
"Avoid obfuscating the email address of the submitter as this adds additional work when searching logs.\n"
"\n"
"|`Reviewed by:`\n"
"|The name and e-mail address of the person or people that reviewed the change; for developers, just the username on the FreeBSD cluster. If a patch was submitted to a mailing list for review, and the review was favorable, then just include the list name.\n"
"\n"
"|`Tested by:`\n"
"|The name and e-mail address of the person or people that tested the change; for developers, just the username on the FreeBSD cluster.\n"
"\n"
"|`Approved by:`\n"
"a|\n"
"\n"
"The name and e-mail address of the person or people that approved the change; for developers, just the username on the FreeBSD cluster.\n"
"\n"
"There are several cases where approval is customary:\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3288
#, no-wrap
msgid "while a new committer is under mentorship\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3289
#, no-wrap
msgid "commits to an area of the tree to which you do not usually commit\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3290
#, no-wrap
msgid "during a relese cycle\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3294
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"committing to a repo where you do not hold a commit bit (e.g. src committer committing to docs)\n"
"\n"
"While under mentorship, get mentor approval before the commit. Enter the mentor's username in this field, and note that they are a mentor:\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3301
msgid ""
"....  Approved by: username-of-mentor (mentor)  ....  If a team approved "
"these commits then include the team name followed by the username of the "
"approver in parentheses. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: documentation/content/en/articles/committers-guide/_index.adoc:3343
msgid ""
"....  Approved by: re (username)  ....  |`Obtained from:` |The name of the "
"project (if any) from which the code was obtained. Do not use this line for "
"the name of an individual person.  |`Fixes:` |The git short hash as returned "
"by `git rev-parse --short` (or SVN revision number, for ports) and the title "
"line of a commit that is fixed by this change.  |`MFC after:` |To receive an "
"e-mail reminder to MFC at a later date, specify the number of days, weeks, "
"or months after which an MFC is planned.  |`MFC to:` |If the commit should "
"be merged to a subset of stable branches, specify the branch names.  |`MFC "
"with:` |If the commit should be merged together with a previous one in a "
"single MFC commit (for example, where this commit corrects a bug in the "
"previous change), specify the corresponding revision number.  |`MFH:` |A "
"ports quarterly branch name, to request approval for merge.  |`Relnotes:` |"
"If the change is a candidate for inclusion in the release notes for the next "
"release from the branch, set to `yes`.  |`Security:` |If the change is "
"related to a security vulnerability or security exposure, include one or "
"more references or a description of the issue. If possible, include a VuXML "
"URL or a CVE ID.  |`Event:` |The description for the event where this commit "
"was made. If this is a recurring event, add the year or even the month to "
"it. For example, this could be `FooBSDcon 2019`. The idea behind this line "
"is to put recognition to conferences, gatherings, and other types of meetups "
"and to show that these are useful to have. Please do not use the `Sponsored "
"by:` line for this as that is meant for organizations sponsoring certain "
"features or developers working on them.  |`Sponsored by:` |Sponsoring "
"organizations for this change, if any. Separate multiple organizations with "
"commas. If only a portion of the work was sponsored, or different amounts of "
"sponsorship were provided to different authors, please give appropriate "
"credit in parentheses after each sponsor name. For example, `Example.com "
"(alice, code refactoring), Wormulon (bob), Momcorp (cindy)` shows that Alice "
"was sponsored by Example.com to do code refactoring, while Wormulon "
"sponsored Bob's work and Momcorp sponsored Cindy's work. Other authors were "
"either not sponsored or chose not to list sponsorship.  |`Differential "
"Revision:` |The full URL of the Phabricator review. This line __must be the "
"last line__. For example: `https://reviews.freebsd.org/D1708`.  |`Signed-off-"
"by:` |ID certifies compliance with https://developercertificate.org/"
msgstr ""

